From 2cdf734412a9274cce266b7ad3a6366ffb76d6fe Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Dr. Hannah Sanford-Crane" <hannah@maadscientist.com>
Date: Thu, 5 Mar 2026 03:15:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Glycan Phase 5 v5: Davis CH-pi explicit + WGA subsite maps
 final

- Davis receptor: add TEM CH-pi contacts (n_CHP=3 for Glc, per Eades 2026)
  Physical basis: anthracene platforms make CH-pi with C1,C3,C5 axial Hs
  Re-anchor DG0_Davis=-19.30 kJ/mol
- Davis-Gal/Man: axial OH displaces sugar from beta-face -> n_CHP=1, n_HB=2
  Residuals: Gal=+0.50, Man=+0.20 kJ/mol (prev: -3.3, -3.6)
- Davis-2dGlc: n_HB=0, n_CHP=3 (C2-OH absent; beta-face intact)
  Residual: -0.90 kJ/mol (unchanged)
- WGA secondary subsites v4: subsite C NHAc solvent-exposed (beta1->4 geometry)
  (GlcNAc)2-4 all HIGH conf, MAE=0.88 kJ/mol
- Phase 5 v5 metrics: HIGH conf R2=0.984, MAE=0.42, RMSE=0.57 kJ/mol (n=15)
- Full panel R2=0.836, MAE=1.20, RMSE=2.52 kJ/mol (n=21)
- Known gaps (not modeled, flagged LOW/MEDIUM):
  ConA trimannoside: +6.0 kJ/mol (branched cooperative term)
  PNA-GalNAc: +9.2 kJ/mol (NHAc disrupts PNA pharmacophore)
- parameters_v23.py: add DG0_Davis, CH_PI_EPS dispatch table, K_DESOLV dict
---
 glycan/parameters_v23.py            |  63 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 glycan/phase5/contact_maps_v5.py    |  36 ++++++++++++++++
 glycan/phase5/phase5_v5_results.csv |  22 ++++++++++
 glycan/phase5/phase5_v5_scatter.png | Bin 0 -> 159067 bytes
 4 files changed, 121 insertions(+)
